---

As summer nears its end devs and folk gathered in Shibuya for another Tokyo Indies. Read on to learn what games were shown this month!

!embed https://vimeo.com/172959118
<iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/172959118?app_id=122963" width="772" height="434" frameborder="0" title="Ritual of the Moon teaser" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>

[Kara Stone](https://twitter.com/karaastone)'s [Ritual of the Moon](http://ritualofthemoon.tumblr.com/) is a game you play five minutes a day for twenty-eight days. A witch banished to the moon reflects on her life on earth and decides whether her former home is worth saving.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VjHvmOidbi8
<iframe width="772" height="434" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VjHvmOidbi8?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Sea](https://twitter.com/umikazemarin)'s [Fragment of Marine](https://ec.nintendo.com/JP/ja/titles/70010000011749) is a "circle action" game where your character runs along rails and careful timing and mode switching are the key to solving puzzles. 

!img homecoming.jpg

[Kotarou Dendaira](https://twitter.com/kotaro_stajiotk)'s [Home coming](https://novelgame.jp/games/show/983) is a visual novel where when and how you save affects the story and the final ending.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P7nO43gdxFg
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/P7nO43gdxFg?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>

[Arcane Circus](https://twitter.com/arcanecircus)'s [Kaijack: Card Attack!](http://kaijackcardattack.com/) is a game combining elements of poker and blackjack with city-destroying giant monsters.

!embed https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A0v29CL0hD4
<iframe width="612" height="344" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/A0v29CL0hD4?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen></iframe>


[Azumagoro](https://twitter.com/azumagoro)'s [ReRotation](https://rerotation.wixsite.com/rerotation) combines elements of monster collection and digital card games to create a strategic battle experience.

!embed https://vimeo.com/276855421
<iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/276855421?app_id=122963" width="772" height="434" frameborder="0" title="Like Roots In The Soil  // Egx Rezzed / AMaze // 2018" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>


[The Space Backyard](https://twitter.com/spacebackyard)'s [Roots in the Soil](https://spacebackyard.itch.io/like-roots-in-the-soil) is a game about two protagonists in different worlds. Which one you see to the end is decided just by changing your point of view - literally.

That was it for this month's Tokyo Indies! Catch you again next month. ðŸŽ®
